<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7621369>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A. Serra do Conduru State Park, general view of the type locality of Wittmackia conduruensis. B. Natural population in the habitat growing as epiphyte. C. Michelin Ecological Reserve, general view of the type locality of Wittmackia guedesiae. D. Natural population in the habitat growing as epiphyte. Photos:A, C) E.H.Souza, B) E.M.C.Leme, D) T.A.Silva." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7621369/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7621375>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Wittmackia conduruensis. A. Habit. B. Leaf in adaxial and abaxial view. C. Leaf apex and adaxial view. D. Leaf apex and abaxial view. E. Leaf sheath showing the adaxial face. F. Median portion of the leaf blade in abaxial view highlighting the central channel. G. Inflorescence. H. Inflorescence details. I. Peduncle. J. Flowers. K. Floral bracts. L. Peduncle bracts. M. Petals. N. Sepals. O. Stamens. P. Stigma. Q. Ovary. Photos: E.H. Souza. Bars: A = 6 cm; B–D, F–G = 3 cm; E–H = 1.5 cm; I–J = 7 mm; K–L = 6 mm; M = 5 mm; N = 4 mm; P–Q = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7621375/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

